"{\"uid\": \"egyptindependent.com-laila-el-shantnawy-makes-history-as-first-egyptian-woman-arbitrator-for-paris-2024-olympics\", \"text\": \"Laila al-Shantnawy has been appointed as an arbitrator on the Special Court for Sport for the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.  This historic appointment marks a significant milestone as she becomes the first Egyptian woman to hold this position since the court's inception, according to theWomen of Egyptwebsite.  Moreover, al-Shantnawy is the sole representative from both Africa and the Arab world on the court for this Olympic edition. A distinguished Egyptian lawyer, arbitrator, and mediator, she holds degrees from Cairo University and institutions in Germany and England.  Expressing her profound pride and fulfillment, al-Shantnawy shared that serving as an arbitrator at the Paris Games has been a lifelong aspiration.\"}"